@*
WHAT: new custom app for topics to scroll across the page with an icon
WHY: we needed an elegant way to show multiple topics without taking up too much space
WHERE: Accu2025 > SITE > Demos & WIP > AccuScroller
WAS: built in Tailwind Playground, https://play.tailwindcss.com/BUOebeYJGS

Note on how Seamless Loop works: In our CSS Keyframes, our marquee animation moves from translateX(0%) to translateX(-50%).
Because we rendered the items twice inside the w-max container, the container is 200% the width of the actual content.
By the time the animation hits the 50% mark, the "second" set of icons is exactly where the "first" set started.
The browser resets to 0% instantly, but because the visuals are identical at those two points,
the creates the illusion of a seamless, continuous loop.

FUTURE IDEAS: implement more settings AND allow them as the module-default OR item-level
e.g. add Tailwind's class for animate-bounce at the module level and it gets added to 
all items
Note that this gets confusing because both Tw and FontAwesome (FA) have similar options for 
things like size, animation, etc. And since Tw requires more work to make the options 
available at theme/app compile time, implementing features like this is actually easier 
using the FA options, https://docs.fontawesome.com/web/style/animate
*@

@inherits AppCode.Razor.AppRazor
@using AppCode.Data
@using AppCode.Razor
@using ToSic.Razor.Blade
@using Accuraty.Libraries.AccuLadder

@{
  var topics = AsList<Content>(MyItems);

  // wire up our .css file
  // We need the path+filename of the Razor .cshtml for this View
  var myViewSpecs = App.Data.GetOne<Custom.Data.CustomItem>(MyView.Id, skipTypeCheck: true);
  // Accuraty standard is to use the same base filename
  // The css file gets connect to the page in the last line of this file, with a priority to load after all other stylesheets
  string cssFile = $"{MyView.Folder.Url}/{myViewSpecs.String("Path").Replace(".cshtml", ".css")}";
}

<div class="accuscroll-wrapper bg-gray-950 overflow-hidden mt-24 lg:mt-32">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl py-24 px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-12 gap-y-16 items-center md:grid-cols-12">

      @* 1. Header Column - Partial Include *@
      <div class="col-span-1 lg:max-w-md md:col-span-5 *:text-gray-100">
        @Html.Partial("AccuScroller__Heading-Basic.cshtml", MyHeader)
      </div>

      @* 2. Content Column - Masking + Container soft fade on edges *@
      <div
        class="relative flex flex-col gap-y-10 overflow-hidden md:col-span-7 mask-[linear-gradient(to_right,transparent_0,black_15%,black_85%,transparent_100%)]"
      >
        @* Row Repeater - each row has three topics and then switchs animation type upon new row *@
        @{
          // Group the topics into lists of 3 for each row
          var topicRows = topics.Select((x, i) => new { Index = i, Value = x})
            .GroupBy(x => x.Index / 3)
            .Select(g => g.Select(x => x.Value).ToList())
            .ToList();
          
          int rowIndex = 0;
        }
        @foreach (var rowItems in topicRows)
        {
          // Alternate animation class based on row index
          var animationClass = (rowIndex % 2 == 0) ? "animate-(--animate-marquee)" : "animate-(--animate-marquee-reverse)";
        
          <div class="flex w-max @animationClass transform-gpu hover:[animation-play-state:paused]">
            @* SEAMLESS LOOP : We render the row content twice *@
            @for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++)
            {
              @* Only hide from screen readers if it's the second iteration (i == 1) *@
              var isDuplicate = (i == 1);

              <div class="flex gap-x-12 items-center pr-12" @(isDuplicate ? "aria-hidden=\"true\"" : "")>
                @foreach (var topic in rowItems)
                {
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-x-3 whitespace-nowrap" @Kit.Toolbar.Default(topic)>
                    @* .IconColor dropdown options: text-blue-400 text-green-400 text-red-400 text-yellow-400 text-white *@
                    <i class="fas @topic.Icon @(Text.Has(topic.IconSize) ? $"fa-{topic.IconSize}" : "") text-@topic.IconColor"
                      aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    <span class="font-medium text-gray-100">@topic.Title</span>
                  </div>
                }
              </div>
            }
          </div>

          rowIndex++;
        }
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<link href="@cssFile" @Kit.Page.AssetAttributes(priority: 200, position: "bottom") type="text/css" rel="stylesheet">
